        <person:biography visibility="public" path="/0000-0001-5402-6191/biography">
            <common:created-date>2016-04-15T20:50:01.396Z</common:created-date>
            <common:last-modified-date>2018-08-08T15:14:09.901Z</common:last-modified-date>
            <personal-details:content>I am geologist/paleoecologist and my long-term research interest is the natural history of the Amazon region and its seaward extension, the Amazon Fan. In my research I have mostly focused on western Amazonia (Colombia, Peru, Brazil) and my most substantial scientific contributions were to identify the crucial role of Andean uplift on the evolution of Amazonia during the Cenozoic and to recognize the Neogene marine incursions into this region. 

In recent years my work concentrated on interdisciplinary cooperation and data integration. This is best exemplified in a Science paper published in 2010 where the links between biodiversity patterns and mountain uplift are explained. Other examples of my multidisciplinary work are the books Amazonia, Landscape and Species Evolution (2010) and Mountains, Climate and Biodiversity (2018), both published with Wiley-Blackwell.

Between 2011 and 2015 I coordinated an ERC funded research project in the framework of Climamazon, a European - Brazilian collaboration that investigated Amazon drainage basin. In this project we studied the onset and development of the Amazon River and its effects on primary productivity in the western Atlantic. Since summer 2016, I participate as senior scientist in the ERC funded project entitled MAGIC [http://cordis.europa.eu/project/rcn/197271_en.html]. In this context I supervise 1 post-doc student, a PhD student with a grant from the Chinese Scholarship Council, two MSc students and one BSc student. 

In 2017 I acted as advisor to the Ecuadorian government and was board member of Ikiam Universidad regional Amazonia. This position was through direct appointment by presidential decree of Rafael Correa Delgado. In the context of my work in Ecuador my Ecuadorian colleagues and I put together a proposal to organize a celebratory conference in Quito in honour of the 250th birth anniversary of Alexander von Humboldt. This proposal was accepted by the International Biogeographic Society, and in 2019 the Universidad de San Francisco in Quito will host the interim meeting of the society. 

In 2018 I obtained a fellowship through the Chinese Academy of Sciences - International Fellowship Initiative (PIFI), which is intended to develop active collaboration with the research group of the late professor Zhang (Chinese Academy of Sciences). This year I have also been appointed Associate Editor at the Journal of Biogeography, and I am lead editor of a special issue on the "Legacy of Alexander von Humboldt" which is to be published in the Journal of Biogeography in 2019.</personal-details:content>
        </person:biography>
